-- China Stocks: Citic Securities, Datang International, Kweichow
-- B y   S h a r o n   C h e n
-- 2012-06-05T08:40:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-05/china-stocks-citic-securities-datang-international-kweichow.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in China trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
as of the close.  The  Shanghai Composite Index (SHCOMP) , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, rose 3.37 points, or 0.2 percent, to
2,311.92. The  CSI 300 Index (SHSZ300)  declined less than 0.1 percent to
2,558.84.  Defensive stocks:  North China Pharmaceutical Co. (600812)  (600812
CH) advanced 4.5 percent to 7.40  yuan , the highest close since
March 13.  Datang International Power Generation Co. (601991)  (601991 CH)
climbed 4 percent to 5.24 yuan, the most since Feb. 16.  Kweichow
Moutai Co. (600519)  (600519 CH), the nation’s biggest maker of baijiu
liquor, rose 1.8 percent to 240.80, a record close.  Investors bought shares of companies whose earnings may be
more resilient in an economic slowdown.  China Vanke Co. (200002)  (000002 CH), the country’s largest
developer, advanced 0.8 percent to 9.11 yuan, the first gain in
four days, after May sales jumped 44 percent from the previous
month.  Citic Securities Co. (600030)  (600030 CH) retreated 1.6 percent to
13.13 yuan.  Haitong Securities Co. (600837)  (600837 CH) slid 1.3 percent
to 10.06 yuan. The 21st Century Herald said regulators may
suspend a plan to allow foreign companies to list in Shanghai.  Qingdao Haier Co. (600690)  (600690 CH) advanced 1.6 percent to 11.83
yuan. The  finance ministry  said China will offer subsidies for
the purchase of energy-saving refrigerators and washing
machines.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Chen in Singapore at 
